Shares of the following companies
had  unusual (TWSE)  moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index fell 2.3 percent to 6,764.59, the lowest
close since Aug. 27, 2009.  Epistar Corp. (2448)  (2448 TT) sank 4.8 percent to NT$61.10, the
most since Nov. 23. Nomura Holdings Inc. recommended not buying
Asian light-emitting diode stocks. Deteriorating profitability
for LED backlighting will continue in 2012 and beyond, while
longer term general lighting will be another tough market for
LED makers, Anne Lee, analyst at Nomura, wrote in a report.  Sino-American Silicon Products Inc. (5483)  (5483 TT) declined 6.2
percent to NT$39.10, the lowest close since Nov. 24. The company
plans to sign a loan of about $360 million equivalent by the end
of the year to fund the purchase of Covalent Materials Corpâ€™s
wafer unit, said a person familiar with the matter who declined
to be identified because the details are private.  To contact the reporter on this story:
